webpackJsonp([0xf81a0fc1c7da],{478:function(e,n){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"I better remember this.",author:"Ricardo Molina"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/ric/myprojs/gatsby-blog/src/pages/simple-note-taking-from-the-command-line/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>This is a simple function that can be called from the command line, just like if it was a regular command. It is a quick way of taking notes and storing them in a text file.</p>\n<p>Just add the following lines to your <code>~/.bashrc</code>:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code># My function to take quick notes on useful commands\nnotes() {\n    echo $1 >> $HOME/notes.md\n}</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>It can be used like this:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>$ notes "my_command -which -I -want -to remember"</code></pre>\n      </div>\n<p>You can read your notes like this:</p>\n<div class="gatsby-highlight">\n      <pre class="language-none"><code>$ more ~/notes.md</code></pre>\n      </div>',frontmatter:{title:"Simple note taking from the command line",date:"September 30, 2017"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/simple-note-taking-from-the-command-line/"}}}});
